====Affix====
{{ja-noun|がい}}

# {{defdate|from 900}} [[cliff]]

===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|がけ|yomi=k|alt=厓}}

Shift from older pronunciation ''kake''. First attested in 1280.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2}}</ref>

May be a shift in usage from compounding element ''kake'' as in the synonymous terms {{m|ja|懸路|tr=kakeji}}, {{m|ja|懸道|tr=kakemichi||cliff road, steep mountain road}},<ref name="KDJ2"/> where the ''kake'' comes from verb {{m|ja|かける|懸ける|tr=kakeru|to set into; to set across}}, from the way the road would be set into the cliff or mountain.

The change from ''kake'' to ''gake'' apparently happened some time during the {{w|Edo period}} (1603–1868). This term is recorded as ''Caqe'' (then-current Portuguese orthography for modern romanization ''kake'') in the 1603 ''{{w|Nippo Jisho}}'' Japanese-Portuguese dictionary.<ref name="N">{{R:Nippo Jisho original}}, available via Google Books [https://books.google.com/books?id=TFJAAQAAMAAJ&vq=caqa&pg=PA37#v=onepage&q=caqe&f=false here], right-hand column, 12th entry</ref>

